#originalTopic=Debate:_Public_insurance_option_in_US_health_care
 Public option is really about making way for a single-payer system Gregory Mankiw. "The pitfalls of the public option". New York Times. June 27, 2009: "the public plan would likely undercut private firms and get an undue share of the market. [...] President Obama might not be disappointed if that turned out to be the case. During the presidential campaign, he said, 'If I were designing a system from scratch, I would probably go ahead with a single-payer system.'"
